(fifthQuint)A Registry Study on Xiyanping(a Chinese Medicine Injection) Used in Fifty Hospitals.

 It is very common that Chinese Medicine Injection used in hospitals in mainland China.

 However safety problems rose in recent years.

 There could be many uncertain factors influence Chinese Medicine Injection in clinical practice.

 In order to ensure the safety of public drug use and lower drug-induced risks, a registry study for Xiyanping injection safety surveillance with 20000 patients will be conducted from Jan.

2012 to Dec.

2015.

 Eligibility criteria Patients who will use Xiyanping injection in selected hospitals.

